tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Renal function is impaired as indicated by elevated creatinine. Alkaline phosphatase is also elevated, which may suggest possible hepatobiliary or bone involvement. Triglycerides are mildly elevated. Other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver transaminases, and proteins, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal and hepatobiliary status.
